# GitHub doesn't natively recognize Pine Script (.pine) for syntax
# highlighting, so this maps it to Python's highlighter instead — closer
# fit than JavaScript given Pine's indentation-based blocks (no braces).
# Trade-off: this also makes the repo's language stats bar report the file
# as "Python" instead of leaving it unclassified — GitHub doesn't offer a
# way to borrow highlighting without also affecting the stats bar.
*.pine linguist-language=Python
